Text.string: Typhon's... dead.
We can't let him be forgotten!
Aggghghgh!
Do not forget the detonator, Vault Hunter.
Now, I have already determined the optimal place from which to launch Typhon's memorial rocket. Head there now.
He's dead. He's freakin' DEAD. Like, forever dead.
You're getting yourself all worked up.
But I never got to thank him for creating me!
Well, it's too late now. There, feel better?
GAH! Why aren't you sad?! He created you, too!
Sadness is a pointless emotion. As are all emotions. I have sent the Vault Hunter to launch a rocket to placate you. This mission, and Typhon's death, mean nothing to me. Just so we're clear.

On your way to the optimal rocket launch site, you will pass one of Typhon's old bases. How... sentimental. The last ECHO logs Typhon ever recorded are there. However, so is Maliwan. You must strike them down and recover the ECHO logs. Only then will we pay a fitting tribute to our master.
Vault Hunter, he's... DEAD! Typhon's dead! The walls are closing in! Oh man, oh man, oh man! Grouse! What was I supposed to ask the Vault Hunter to do?!
Typhon's last ECHO and testament. It is pointless to listen to them, but these damn things autoplay. How distracting.
Grouse, Sparrow, if you're listening to this, I croaked! Had to happen sometime. But hey, I lived a full life. I got some parting words for ya. In the next ECHO!
Sparrow: you made me laugh, and like I always say, “A life without laughter, it's like a sky without stars.” The galaxy's a dangerous place, and we need more bots like you. So don't grieve. Dance!
Whatever you say, Typhon. I'll miss you! I'm dancing! [sob] I'm cry-dancing!
Curious, I'm sensing an additional ECHO log nearby, but it is... moving...
The beast has the ECHO log. Exterminate it!
The final ECHO log. Whatever parting words Typhon left were wasted moments, in my correct opinion. Damn autoplay.

Grouse, you could out-sour a lemon's armpit. Because I designed you that way! I needed someone to push me to survive! But I'm gone now. So, go have some fun, buddy! You don't gotta be a lemon no more! Experience joy. Play some games! Go on a trip. Or dance! Just promise you'll take care of Sparrow. He needs you! But you need him, too! You're my best buds! Farewell.
Grouse, you look sick. You okay, buddy?
Hghhhhhh! He's GONE! And I'll never SEE HIM AGAIN! Ughghghgh! I'm SAAAAAD!
Quiet down! Do you want Maliwan to scrap us?
Yowza. Vault Hunter, go assemble the rocket. I'm gonna hug my buddy Grouse.||—Come here, you grouchy son of a bitch!
Grouse is... having a tough time, but he told ME to tell YOU to put Typhon's final ECHO logs in the rocket. Then his legacy will be complete.
I am DROWNED in EMOTION! If I were a BIRD I would FLY INTO THE SUN!
Now the detonator, Vault Hunter.
Grouse, come on out! It's time to launch Typhon's rocket!
Can't... sad...
You heard Typhon. Happiness IS survival. So watch this damn rocket or I'm gonna kill you!
Fine.
Amazing! Grouse, what the hell?! You're still crying!
I feel... happy-sad. It is... confusing.
I'm freaking out. I'm freaking out. Walls closing in... hrghgh...
Come on back, Vault Hunter. Grouse and I want to thank you in person!
Typhon is gone, but thanks to you, he'll always be remembered.
We will be the stewards of this planet, as Typhon would have wanted.
Take all the Eridium! We don't need it.
Now, I will... have some... “fun”.
I'll put on some music for ya!
Try it, buddy!
No.
Dancing keeps your gears in shape! It's efficient...
Fine...

As you can see, Sparrow is grief-stricken by Typhon's death and thus useless to me. An utterly pointless emotion, grief. Nevertheless, if Sparrow is to be of any use, we must memorialize Typhon. Grab those rocket parts I WAS saving for our defense. I can think of no better tribute than to light the sky on fire.
How... enjoyable, somehow. I'm furious I'm enjoying this... but I am. Why can't I stop spinning?
Partyyyy!
The fun is over.
You're a natural! Teach me that move.
No.||—Fine.
Now I have to spend an eternity with YOU!
Come now, it might not be THAT long.
Really? Why's that?
Maliwan might scrap you tomorrow.
